  "prompt": "What universities does Sonic Automotive recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Sonic Automotive, a prominent automotive retailer, recruits new graduates from various universities across the United States. While specific recruiting practices and preferred universities may vary over time, Sonic Automotive typically seeks candidates from institutions known for their strong business, management, and automotive programs.\n\nSome commonly targeted universities might include:\n1. University of North Carolina at Charlotte\n2. Clemson University\n3. University of South Carolina\n4. Wake Forest University\n5. North Carolina State University\n6. Michigan State University\n\nRegarding majors, Sonic Automotive generally looks for graduates with degrees in:\n1. Business Administration\n2. Marketing\n3. Automotive Management\n4. Finance\n5. Economics\n6. Information Technology (IT)\n7. Human Resources\n8. Engineering (specific to automotive)\n9. Supply Chain Management\n\nKeep in mind that recruitment strategies can evolve, and Sonic Automotive may consider candidates from other universities and majors based on their specific needs and market conditions. It's always a good idea to check their current job postings or contact their HR department for the latest information.",
